<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9737> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9737" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Additions and Corrections. A milestone of the Via Domitia, found in 1949 at Pont de Treilles in the department of Aude at about twenty miles from Narbo, and inscribed Cn. Domitius Cn. f. Ahenobarbus imperator XX, raises the probability that his proconsulate extended until the founding of Narbo in 118 and that his triumph was not celebrated until that or even the following year (P.-M. Duval, \"A propos d'un miliaire de Cnaeus Domitius Ahenobarbus Imperator,\" CRAI 1951, 161-168). It follows that the term of the proconsulate and the date of the triumph of Q. Fabius Maximus Allobrogicus should also be placed in thesse years. Both triumphs precede the triumph of Metellus Delmaticus in 117." ;
	dprr:hasID 9737 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8988> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8988" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 739" ;
	dprr:hasID 8988 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3577> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3577" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Successor: see below, on Scaurus: and above, Tribunes of the Plebs, on Domitius. Suet. Nero 2.1; cf. Ascon. 21 C; and note 7." ;
	dprr:hasID 3577 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3376> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3376" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "As Scaurus was Princeps Senatus in 112 (Sall. Iug. 25.4), he must have been appointed by the Censors of 115, although, as Mommsen pointed out (Str. 3.970), there had not been a certain example of a Princeps Senatus who was not a patrician Censor or ex-Censor (see however 125, Censors, on P. Cornelius Lentulus). It seems probable that no patrician ex-Censors remained alive in 115. The latest reference to one is that to Servilius Caepio in 125 (see 125, Censors), the date of whose death remains unknown (see Cic. Att. 12.20.2; and 105, Quaestors). Scaurus was repeatedly reappointed and his position is often mentioned (Cic. Rab. Perd. 21; Scaur. 1.46; De Or. 2.197; Val. Max. 4.4.11; 8.5.2; Ascon. 18, and 22 C; Plin. NH 36.116)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3376 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3375> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3375" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Lex. Agr. of 111, CIL 1\n     .2.585, lines 28, 85-89; Fast. Ant., Degrassi 162f. ([L.] Caecili. Q. f. n. Mete., Cn. D[omiti.- - - -]); Cic. Verr. 2.1.143; Val. Max. 2.9.9). See Degrassi 127, 474f. They removed 32 persons from the Senate, including Licinius Geta, Cos. 116, and Marius' friend Cassius Subaco (Cic. Cluent. 119, and 121; Liv. Per. 62,{532} and 63; Val. Max. 2.9.9; Plut. Mar. 5.3-4), and banished the ars ludicra from the city with the exceptions of the Latin tibicen and singer and the ludus talarius (Cassiod. Chr.). They chose M. Aemilius Scaurus\n     \n      2\n     \n     Princeps Senatus (Sall. Iug. 25.4; Plin. NH 8.223)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3375 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3329> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3329" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul (Act. Tr.). Completed his campaign in Gaul and celebrated a triumph over the Arverni (Act. Tr., Degrassi 82f., 560; Flor. 1.37.5; Eutrop. 4.22; cf. Vell. 2.10.2; Liv. Per. 61; Suet. Nero 2; Grueber, CRRBM 1.151; 2.258f.). He built the Via Domitia and organized the province (see Cic. Font. 18)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3329 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3306> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3306" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul (Act. Tr. for 120). Continued along with the Consul Fabius the wars against the Allobroges and the Arverni (see 122, Consuls, and 120, Promagistrates)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3306 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3278> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3278" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Brut. 99-100; Fast. Ant., Degrassi 162f. ([Cn.] D[- - - -], C. Fan[- - - -]); Plin. NH 2.99; Obseq. 32; Chr. 354 (Enobarbo et Fanno); Fast. Hyd. (Ahenobarbo et Faenio), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Fannius, CIL 1\n     .2.658. See Degrassi 126, 472f. Domitius succeeded Sextius in Gaul, where he was victorious over the Salluvii, and then engaged in war against the Allobroges and the Arverni (Liv. Per. 61; Vell. 2.10.2, and 39.1; Strabo 4.2.3; Val. Max. 9.6.3; Suet. Nero 1.2; 2.1; Flor. 1.37.4-6; App. Celt. 12; Eutrop. 4.22; Oros. 5.13.2; Jerome Chr. ad ann. 127, p. 146 Helm; see 121 and 120, Promagistrates). Fannius, though elected over Opimius by the aid of C. Gracchus, turned against him, and opposed particularly the proposal to grant citizenship to Latins and Italians (Plut. CG 8.2-3; 11.2-3; 12.1-2; cf. Cic. Brut. 99; De Or. 3.183; FOR 1.246f.)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3278 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3276> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3276" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On Domitius' filiation, see Act. Tr. for 120. Suetonius dates his victories in his consulship, but Livy and Orosius are probably correct in referring them to his proconsulship." ;
	dprr:hasID 3276 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3238> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3238" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The latest date possible for his praetorship." ;
	dprr:hasID 3238 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3222> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3222" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 129, Legates." ;
	dprr:hasID 3222 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3210> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3210" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Aquillius in Asia, probably as a Legatus pro praetore (Holleaux, REA 21 [1919] 1-6, with title {Gr}; cf. IGRP 4.968)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3210 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10064> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10064" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Galleis Arverneis. MRR I.524, III.81-2, Itgenshorst no. 222, Rich no. 222." ;
	dprr:hasID 10064 .
